<h2>AMENITIES</h2>
<h3>Things to do in and around Montgomery</h3>
<p>The Montgomery Community Association administers the area and operates a hockey rink and an outdoor skating rink. The association also hosts bingo and sports programs. The community hall has wheelchair access, a gym, commercial kitchen, stage and meeting room. In the southwest portion of the community is the Shouldice Arena and Athletic Park, complete with a hockey rink, four soccer fields, a baseball field, seven softball fields and three football fields, all available for bookings March through November. Also available is the Shouldice Aquatic Centre, with a pool and dive tank.</p>
<p>To the West lies <a href="/bowness.php">Bowness</a> and to the north, in <a href="/varsity.php">Varsity</a>, is Market Mall, one of Calgary&rsquo;s largest indoor shopping malls, with over 200 stores, including The Bay, Old Navy and Apple Store (the first one to open in Calgary). Built in a racetrack style layout, the mall is easy to navigate. Food is easy to find in the mall as well, with a standard food court, as well as a Moxie's Classic Grill and a Milestones.</p>
<p>Montgomery has an elementary school and a junior high school operated by the CBE.</p>
</div>
